## Learned User Preferences

- Reminder/instruction injections defer until ~70% context-window utilization to preserve provider prompt-cache hits (R1 of `docs/research/gemini-prompt-cache-busting.md`).
- `gitStatus` is omitted entirely from prompt context until git is wired into projects — placeholder/empty `gitStatus` values still bust prompt caches across providers.
- Don't introduce env vars for single-consumer time/threshold knobs with a sane default — hard-code inline (e.g. `dedupEntryTtlSeconds = 3600`); promote to config only when a 2nd consumer needs it.
- `/health/ready` must assert every external capability (Postgres, Redis, S3/R2 via root probe `__health/probe.txt` decoupled from prefix) so capability go-live is verified without manual probes.
- All API Zod schemas remain pure (no refines/superRefines/checks) so they convert cleanly to JSON Schema for OpenAPI; cross-field/conditional rules live outside the schema (controller/service guards or DTO normalisation), never inline on the schema.

## Learned Workspace Facts

- Dev API runs under `vite-plugin-node@8`'s `NestHandler`, whose `if (!app.isInitialized)` guard is non-atomic — `apps/api/app/main.ts` must `await app.init()` + `fastifyInstance.ready()` in bootstrap (dev + prod) so concurrent first requests cannot race-register Fastify routes and crash with `FST_ERR_DUPLICATED_ROUTE` (upstream issue axe-me/vite-plugin-node#33, open since 2022; no NestJS version fixes it — see nestjs/nest#12006). The `unhandledRejection` trap in `main.ts` log-and-skips `FST_ERR_DUPLICATED_ROUTE` as defense in depth so future regressions never reproduce the crash-loop. Regression covered by `apps/api/app/main.race.test.ts`.
- Publication visibility is binary — `Public` + `Private` only; the prior `Unlisted`/secret-token tier was dropped because publication IDs are already opaque, so it duplicated `Private` without UX benefit.
- Read-file dedup uses LangGraph `Store` (Option B): `RedisStore` in dev/staging/prod via NestJS DI, `InMemoryStore` for tests — `wrap*` middleware breaks streaming so was rejected; on Redis 8.
- Socket.IO RPC uses `emitWithAck` pattern (replaced manual `pendingRequests` Map); prod uses `RedisIoAdapter` with `@socket.io/redis-streams-adapter` for horizontal scaling and CSR; dev uses standalone Socket.IO server on `PORT+1` via `DevWebSocketService` without Redis adapter; auth via `server.use()` middleware in gateway `afterInit`; health probes at `/health/live|ready|startup` via `@nestjs/terminus` with custom `RedisHealthIndicator` and `DatabaseHealthIndicator`
- API deployed to Fly.io (`apps/api/fly.prod.toml`) via `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` — image is built+pushed by `docker/build-push-action@v6` to `registry.fly.io/<app>:<sha>` (registry-backed BuildKit cache: `cache-from`/`cache-to type=registry,ref=registry.fly.io/<app>:buildcache,mode=max`), then `flyctl deploy --image` skips Fly's own builder; `apps/api/Dockerfile` (BuildKit syntax 1.20 for `COPY --parents`) pins pnpm via `npm i -g pnpm@${PNPM_VERSION}` (no Corepack), splits `base → deps → build → pruned → runtime`, mounts BuildKit caches for `/pnpm/store` (all stages) and `/app/.nx/cache` (build only), reads `NX_CLOUD_ACCESS_TOKEN` via `--mount=type=secret,id=nx_cloud_token`, installs only the API subgraph via `pnpm install --filter=@taucad/api... --prefer-offline`, runs as non-root `nestjs` (uid 1001), and embeds a `HEALTHCHECK` against `/health/ready`; `.dockerignore` excludes `tarballs/{experiments,comparisons,package,active}` and `apps/api/reports`/`packages/runtime/{reports,occt-reports}` to keep the build context ~430 MB; Better Auth cookie domain is auto-detected from the incoming request (not hardcoded) and uses `sameSite: 'lax'` so UI and API must share a parent domain (custom domains: `tau.new` for prod, `taucad.dev` for staging); Socket.IO has CORS disabled (Fastify handles CORS at the application level via `TAU_FRONTEND_URL` + `ADDITIONAL_CORS_ORIGINS`); Fly cert/app routing gotcha — an `api.<env>` cert can be attached to the WRONG Fly app (e.g. `api.taucad.dev` cert on prod `tau-api` instead of `tau-api-staging`), silently routing requests across environments and producing CORS rejections that look identical to a downed API in the browser console (real 200 with no ACAO is indistinguishable from a 404), so always verify `flyctl certs list -a <app>` matches the intended environment; Supabase free-tier Postgres auto-pauses after 7 days of inactivity and `postgres-js` stringifies the resulting connection failure as `Failed query: CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS "drizzle"\nparams:` because the migrator's first query fires before the connection error surfaces — it masquerades as a permission/role error but is actually connection-level; OTEL SDK bootstraps in `apps/api/app/telemetry/otel.ts`; metrics derived from `@taucad/telemetry` canonical definitions; `PrometheusExporter` on port 9464; traces+logs via OTLP/HTTP to Grafana Cloud; `TelemetryModule` (`@Global`) provides `TracerService` + `@Span()` decorator (only approved tracing approach; `withSpan` removed); `prom-client` fully replaced by `@opentelemetry/api`; Grafana dashboards-as-code in `infra/grafana/` with 10 dashboard JSONs + alert rules, synced to Fly.io Grafana via `apps/api/scripts/sync-grafana-dashboards.sh`; `grafana/otel-lgtm` in `docker-compose.yml` provides local LGTM stack parity with named volumes for data persistence; Drizzle is the only schema-migration authority — never hand-author SQL files under `apps/api/app/database/migrations/` (run `pnpm db:generate` to produce the next `NNNN_<description>.sql` + `meta/NNNN_snapshot.json` from `apps/api/app/database/schema.ts`, then `pnpm db:migrate` to apply); `apps/api/app/api/publications/` is the publications/sharing module (NestJS controller standardised on `nestjs-zod` validation matching the `apps/api/app/api/chat/chat.controller.ts` pattern — explicit request DTOs AND response DTOs validated via Zod, not post-fact validation); `apps/api/app/storage/` houses the R2-compatible upload pipeline (`concat-uint8-arrays.ts` etc.); local dev parity for Cloudflare R2 runs via a MinIO container in `infra/docker-compose.yml` (S3-compatible blob storage) — pin to a known-existing `quay.io/minio/minio:RELEASE.<date>` tag (the registry routinely garbage-collects old release tags, so `not found` errors on `infra:up` mean the tag was reaped); 25 MB blob-size cap on uploaded shareable artifacts; cascade-delete on project removal; always create a new publication and update a pointer rather than mutating in place; visibility model is project-bound with URL-token sharing for unlisted/secret links; publish file allowlist filters out the entire `.tau/` tree EXCEPT `.tau/parameters/*` (everything else inside `.tau/` is editor scratch state and pollutes the storage bucket — drop it at the upload-filter layer, not after the fact); MVP publish flow does NOT render or store a server-side GLB/glTF preview sidecar — the nav-bar share trigger and "share broken project for debugging" workflow both lack live geometry, so requiring a renderable model would block legitimate publish paths (the user-facing rule "sharing controls must NOT gate on render completion" extends to the server pipeline; do not reintroduce a `GlbRenderService.renderGlb` precondition); shared error-code constants live in a single module imported by both API and UI — never hardcode error-code strings on either side; request-derived values (e.g. viewer identity for view tracking, current user, cookies) are resolved via NestJS parameter decorators (e.g. `@OptionalUser()`, custom viewer-identity decorator) so controllers stay idiomatic and resolution logic is encapsulated without inline `service.resolve({ request, reply })` calls polluting controller bodies; per-viewer view-count attribution uses an HMAC-signed opaque viewer cookie (secret read from `TAU_VIEW_COOKIE_SECRET`) so the API can dedupe views per (publication, viewer) without persisting any identifiable info — the cookie is signed locally, never round-trips through user data; if Tau ever needs server-side preview rendering for a future use case, reach for `@taucad/runtime` directly (not `@taucad/cli`) for headless render needs
